name: Sahara Desert Rose (Large) Natural Object
description:
Desert roses are considerately harvested from rare locations under the Sahara desert.  The mineral gypsum forms layer upon layer of spiral crystals colored by the fine powdery Sahara sand.  All desert roses are unique in shape, color and size.  Naturally occuring cracks and crevices are part of their charm.
Sizing: 
Mini: 2"-3" Diam. Weight: 1/2-2 lbs.
Small: 3"-5" Diam. Weight: 3-6 lbs.
Medium: 6"-9" Diam. Weight: 7-15 lbs.
Large: 10"-15" Diam. Weight: 16-30 lbs.
